Rapper YCee has berated Manchester United forward, Mason Greenwood, over assault and rape allegation levelled against him by his partner. Ycee took to his Twitter account to express his disgust for Greenwood’s action noting that he won’t condone such behaviour despite being a Man Utd fan. “Bruh. It is common knowledge that I’m a Man. United fan. Bad behavior remains bad behavior and actions of this nature are extremely inexcusable,” YCee expressed.   Teni gives toddler $1,000     Wizkid speaks on new album     Popular skitmaker Isbae U faces alleged sex-for-skits…   Mason Greenwood was arrested on suspicion of rape and assault on Sunday following posts shared on social media by his girlfriend Harriet Robson. In the images, a series of photographs of her beaten body were posted to her Instagram story, while an audio clip was also shared. - Advertisement - A statement from Greater Manchester Police was shared on Sunday evening, confirming that the Manchester United player had been taken into custody as the police investigate the matter.